epidemics 0.1.0
  • Reference

Run an SIR epidemic model.

Source: R/epi_demic.R
epi_demic.Rd

Run an SIR epidemic model.

Usage

epi_demic(option = c("stochastic", "deterministic"), parameters = list())

Arguments

option

A string, either "deterministic" or "stochastic", for which kind of model to run.

parameters

A parameter list created by the convenience function make_parameters_sir().

Value

A data frame in tidy (long) format with the columns time, S, I

and R for the proportions of individuals infected at each time point.

Examples

epi_demic(
  option = "stochastic",
  parameters = make_parameters_sir(option = "stochastic")
)
